2007-08-14  Bernhard R. Link  <brlink@debian.org>

	* src/main.c (xvsprintf): limit memory allocation
	to 200K when vsnprintf return -1. (i.e. on pre-1999
	systems not distinguising fatal errors and too small
	buffer).

